{{also|Millennium}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From post-classical {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|millennium}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|mīlle||thousand}} + {{m|la|-ennium}} (from {{m|la|annus||year}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mɪˈlɛnɪəm/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-uk-millennium.oga|Audio (UK)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|millennia|millenniums}}

# A [[period]] of [[time]] consisting of one thousand [[year]]s.
#* {{quote-news|date=24 March 2013|author=Dan Pearson|work=The Guardian|passage=Magnolias are some of the most primitive of our flowering trees, and fossils dating back '''millennia''' prove that they have had little need to evolve.}}
# {{lb|en|Christianity}} The period of one thousand years during which Christ will reign on earth (according to Millenarianist interpretations).
#* {{quote-book|year=1911|author={{w|Saki}}|chapter=Tobermory|title=The Chronicles of Clovis|passage=An archangel ecstatically proclaiming the '''Millennium''', and then finding that it clashed unpardonably with Henley and would have to be indefinitely postponed, could hardly have felt more crestfallen than Cornelius Appin at the reception of his wonderful achievement.}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1971|author={{w|Keith Thomas (historian)|Keith Thomas}}|title=Religion and the Decline of Magic|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=2012|page=137|passage=the end of the world would be heralded by a series of spectacular and symbolic events […]. According to most commentators, this '''millennium''' had already begun.}}
#* {{quote-book|year=2011|author={{w|Norman Davies}}|title=Vanished Kingdoms|publisher=Penguin|year_published=2012|page=117|passage=Conrad's later years unfolded in the shadow of the coming '''Millennium''', when the end of the world was forecast.}}
# A period of universal happiness, peace or prosperity; a [[utopia]].
#* {{quote-book|year=1902|author={{w|William James}}|title=The Varieties of Religious Experience|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=2008|page=318|passage=But the aggressive members of society are always tending to become bullies, robbers, and swindlers; and no one believes that such a state of things as we now live in is the '''millennium'''.}}
# {{lb|en|with definite article}} The year in which one period of one thousand years ends and another begins, especially the year 2000.

